-- Citigroup Said to Pay $75 Million to Settle SEC Subprime Case
-- Bill Koenig
-- 2010-07-29T17:59:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/citigroup-agrees-to-pay-75-million-to-end-sec-probe-of-subprime-exposure.html

          
          
             The U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission today accused Citigroup Inc. with misleading
investors about the companyâ€™s exposure to subprime mortgage-
related assets and also said Citigroup agreed to pay a $75
million penalty.  
 The SEC also accused one current and one former executive
for their roles in causing Citigroup to make the misleading
statements in an SEC filing. The information was in an e-mailed
statement.   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
